Phase 9 wave 16 (Lever 3) is the 8bpp end-to-end pass. This patch is
sub-phase 16.3: drop the SDL3-DOS VESA mode-enumeration cap from "16" to
"8" so SDL3-DOS picks an INDEX8 mode (320x240x8 mode 0x10F on Cirrus +
UNIVBE 6.70, or 640x480x8 mode 0x101 on Mach64) instead of the wave-15
16bpp mode. Halves the per-frame VRAM bandwidth (614 KB -> 307 KB on the
g2k Pentium OverDrive 83 MHz reference HW, the dominant cost on real
hardware per dosbox_not_perf_proxy.md memory + docs/PHASE8-FINDINGS.md).

This patch alone DOES NOT make the engine render correctly at 8bpp — the
NXEngine renderer still produces RGB565 surfaces. The renderer-side 8bpp
path (master-palette loader, INDEX8 blit primitives, cmod LUT) is
sub-phase 16.2, expected to land as patches 0073/0074. The integration
test (16.1 + 16.2 + 16.3 all applied) is the only meaningful end-to-end
validation; this patch in isolation will produce visual corruption or
fall back to whatever bpp SDL3-DOS finds available — that's expected and
documented in the wave-16 spec (/tmp/wave-16-spec.md §3) as a known
partial-integration state, not a 16.3 bug.

Also adds a single grep'able LOG_INFO line in Renderer::initVideo so
DEBUG.LOG records that the engine asked for 8bpp. Pairs with the
companion SDL-side WAVE16-MODESET / WAVE16-FB-FIRSTFLUSH lines in
SDLDBG.LOG (patches/SDL/0026) — three lines together confirm the cap
flip propagated end-to-end.

See docs/PHASE9-WAVE-14-PLAN.md §5 for the wave-16 plan and
/tmp/wave-16-spec.md §3 for the implementation spec this patch executes.

Predicted bandwidth halving: 614 KB/frame -> 307 KB/frame.
---
 src/graphics/Renderer.cpp | 12 ++++++++++++
 src/main.cpp              | 28 ++++++++++++++++++----------
 2 files changed, 30 insertions(+), 10 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
index 69d065c..800e758 100644
--- a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
+++ b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
@@ -893,6 +893,18 @@ bool Renderer::initVideo()
   // getResolutions() remain compiled in for possible future use per CLAUDE.md
   // locked decision #5 — we don't rip the table out, we just skip past it.
   window_flags |= SDL_WINDOW_FULLSCREEN;
+
+  // Patch 0072 (Phase 9 wave 16 — Lever 3 mode select, 2026-04-28): record
+  // in DEBUG.LOG that we asked SDL3-DOS for an 8bpp mode via
+  // SDL_HINT_DOS_MAX_BPP. The hint itself is set in main.cpp before SDL_Init;
+  // this line just gives us a single grep'able anchor in the engine log so a
+  // post-run "did wave 16 land?" check is one line of grep. The companion
+  // SDL-side WAVE16-MODESET line in SDLDBG.LOG (patches/SDL/0026) records
+  // what mode SDL3-DOS actually picked under that cap — pairing the two
+  // lines confirms end-to-end engagement.
+  LOG_INFO("Renderer::initVideo: 8bpp mode requested via SDL_HINT_DOS_MAX_BPP=8 "
+           "(wave 16); SDL3-DOS will pick the highest-bpp <= 8 mode at requested "
+           "resolution");
 #endif
 
   const NXE::Graphics::gres_t *res = getResolutions(true);
diff --git a/src/main.cpp b/src/main.cpp
index 49ae2d4..b4d7674 100644
--- a/src/main.cpp
+++ b/src/main.cpp
@@ -402,17 +402,25 @@ int main(int argc, char *argv[])
   SDL_SetHintWithPriority(SDL_HINT_DOS_ALLOW_DIRECT_FRAMEBUFFER, "1", SDL_HINT_OVERRIDE);
 
   // Patch 0041 (Phase 8 perf, 2026-04-26): cap SDL3-DOS VESA mode
-  // enumeration at 16bpp. Without this, SDL3's closest-mode matching picks
-  // 24bpp (mode 0x112 on the g2k Mach64; 32bpp 0x190 on DOSBox-X). 16-cap
-  // forces 0x111 (640×480×16) on Mach64 — drops per-frame framebuffer flush
-  // from 921 KB to 614 KB (~1.5× speedup).
+  // enumeration at a chosen bpp ceiling. Without this, SDL3's closest-mode
+  // matching picks 24bpp (mode 0x112 on the g2k Mach64; 32bpp 0x190 on
+  // DOSBox-X). The cap forces a smaller per-frame framebuffer flush —
+  // bandwidth on the Mach64 PCI bus is the dominant cost on real HW
+  // (docs/PHASE8-FINDINGS.md, dosbox_not_perf_proxy memory).
   //
-  // We don't go to 8bpp (which would be ~3× speedup) because NXEngine's
-  // renderer pipeline isn't palette-ready end-to-end yet — a quick test
-  // produced "Texture doesn't have a palette" errors flooding DEBUG.LOG.
-  // 8bpp end-to-end is Phase 9 lever 3 work; needs palette management on
-  // stage transitions. Tracked in docs/PHASE8-FINDINGS.md.
-  SDL_SetHintWithPriority(SDL_HINT_DOS_MAX_BPP, "16", SDL_HINT_OVERRIDE);
+  // Patch 0072 (Phase 9 wave 16 — Lever 3 mode select, 2026-04-28): cap
+  // dropped to 8bpp. SDL3-DOS will pick INDEX8 320×240×8bpp (mode 0x10F on
+  // Cirrus + UNIVBE) or 640×480×8bpp (mode 0x101 on Mach64), halving VRAM
+  // bandwidth vs the 16bpp wave-15 baseline (614 → 307 KB/frame). Pairs
+  // with the renderer-side 8bpp path landing in patches 0073/0074
+  // (master-palette loader + INDEX8 blit primitives + cmod LUT) which is
+  // sub-phase 16.2 work; this patch (16.3) is the SDL3-DOS mode flip alone.
+  // Without 16.2, the engine still produces RGB565 surfaces and SDL3-DOS
+  // will either render wrong colors or fall back to a higher bpp mode it
+  // happens to find — that's expected and documented in the wave-16 spec
+  // (/tmp/wave-16-spec.md §3) as a partial-integration state, not a 16.3
+  // bug. See docs/PHASE9-WAVE-14-PLAN.md §5 for the wave-16 plan.
+  SDL_SetHintWithPriority(SDL_HINT_DOS_MAX_BPP, "8", SDL_HINT_OVERRIDE);
 
   // Patch 0045 (Phase 9 lever 1, 2026-04-26): prefer LFB over banked at the
   // SDL3-DOS LFB-vs-banked decision (vendor/SDL/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c).
